# Free Website Audit — environment variables
# Copy this file to ".env" for local dev (node dev-server.js), and set the same
# keys in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables for deploy.
# NEVER commit the real .env (it is gitignored).
#
# Every key is OPTIONAL — the audit degrades gracefully. With none set, the
# HTML-based checks (title, meta, H1, alt text, robots, sitemap, HTTPS, links,
# schema, AI search readiness) still run; the keyed checks below report
# "couldn't check". NOTE: the free tool uses NO paid AI API — there is no
# Anthropic/OpenAI key. The AI Search Readiness check is structural (HTML only).

# Google PageSpeed Insights — mobile + desktop performance scores
# Get one free: https://developers.google.com/speed/docs/insights/v5/get-started
PAGESPEED_API_KEY=

# Google Apps Script web-app URL. ONE endpoint does everything email-related —
# no paid service. The script: appends the lead to the "Audit Leads" tab,
# emails the visitor their report (reportHtml), and emails Earvin a notification.
# Deploy a Web App that accepts POST JSON:
# { timestamp, firstName, email, url, perfMobile, perfDesktop, seoScore,
#   technicalScore, flags, subject, reportHtml }
SHEETS_WEBHOOK_URL=
